---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout
  title="Disclaimer | Summit Seeker Trail Information"
  description="Important safety disclaimer and limitation of liability for Summit Seeker hiking trail information. Read before using our trail guides."
>
  <!-- Header/Navigation -->
  <header class="bg-stone-900 border-b border-stone-800 sticky top-0 z-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center h-16">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-white hover:text-emerald-400 transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-emerald-500" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path d="M12 2L2 22h20L12 2zm0 5l6.5 13h-13L12 7z"/>
          </svg>
          <span class="font-black tracking-widest uppercase text-lg">Summit Seeker</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm font-medium">
          <a href="/" class="text-stone-300 hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
          <a href="/about" class="text-stone-300 hover:text-white transition-colors">About</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="text-stone-300 hover:text-white transition-colors">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="flex-1">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-900 via-stone-900 to-stone-900 text-white py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black mb-6">Disclaimer</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-orange-100 leading-relaxed">
          Important safety information and limitations of liability
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

        <!-- Critical Warning -->
        <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-4 border-orange-600 p-6 mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-orange-900 mb-3">‚ö†Ô∏è READ BEFORE HIKING</h2>
          <p class="text-orange-900 font-semibold mb-2">
            Hiking involves inherent risks. You assume all responsibility for your safety.
          </p>
          <p class="text-orange-800 text-sm">
            Summit Seeker provides trail information for educational and planning purposes only.
            This information does not replace proper planning, training, equipment, and judgment.
            Always check current conditions before hiking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Last Updated -->
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 mb-8">
          <strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2026
        </p>

        <!-- Section 1: General Disclaimer -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">1. General Information Disclaimer</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            The information provided on Summit Seeker ("the Website") is for general informational and educational
            purposes only. While we strive for accuracy, we make no representations or warranties of any kind,
            express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability, suitability, or availability of the
            information, products, services, or related graphics contained on the Website.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Trail conditions, regulations, closures, and hazards change frequently due to weather, seasonal factors,
            natural events, and administrative decisions. Information on this Website may be outdated or incomplete.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2: Hiking Risk -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">2. Assumption of Risk</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong>Hiking and outdoor recreation activities are inherently dangerous and involve risks including but not limited to:</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 ml-6 list-disc">
            <li>Falls, injuries, or death from uneven terrain, steep slopes, cliffs, and unstable surfaces</li>
            <li>Severe weather including lightning, hypothermia, heat exhaustion, and frostbite</li>
            <li>Getting lost or disoriented on trails</li>
            <li>Wildlife encounters including bears, moose, snakes, and insects</li>
            <li>Avalanches, rockfall, flooding, and other natural hazards</li>
            <li>Equipment failure or inadequate preparation</li>
            <li>Medical emergencies in remote locations with limited cell service</li>
            <li>Trail closures, private property conflicts, or permit violations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            <strong>By using the information on this Website, you acknowledge and accept these risks.</strong>
            You are solely responsible for your safety, decisions, and actions while hiking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3: No Professional Advice -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">3. Not Professional Advice</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            Summit Seeker does not provide professional hiking guidance, wilderness survival training,
            medical advice, or route-specific safety assessments. The content on this Website should not be
            considered a substitute for:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 ml-6 list-disc mt-4">
            <li>Professional wilderness guide services</li>
            <li>Official park service or forest service information</li>
            <li>Current weather forecasts and avalanche reports</li>
            <li>Personal fitness assessments and medical clearance</li>
            <li>Professional outdoor skills training</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Always verify trail conditions with official sources (National Park Service, US Forest Service,
            state parks) before hiking. Contact local ranger stations for current conditions, closures, and permits.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 4: Limitation of Liability -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, Summit Seeker, its owners, operators, contributors,
            and affiliates shall not be liable for any loss, injury, claim, liability, or damage of any kind
            resulting from:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 ml-6 list-disc mt-4">
            <li>Your use of or reliance on information provided on this Website</li>
            <li>Errors, inaccuracies, or omissions in trail information, maps, or descriptions</li>
            <li>Outdated information due to changing trail conditions or regulations</li>
            <li>Injuries, accidents, or deaths occurring during hiking activities</li>
            <li>Property damage or theft occurring on trails or at trailheads</li>
            <li>Third-party content, links, or recommendations</li>
            <li>Technical issues, website downtime, or data loss</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4 font-semibold">
            YOU USE THIS WEBSITE AND ITS INFORMATION AT YOUR OWN RISK.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5: Third-Party Links -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">5. Third-Party Links and Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            Summit Seeker may contain links to external websites and affiliate partnerships with outdoor gear
            retailers (REI, Amazon, Backcountry, etc.). We are not responsible for the content, accuracy,
            or privacy practices of third-party websites. We may earn commissions from qualifying purchases
            through affiliate links, which helps support our free trail database.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Product recommendations are for informational purposes only. We do not guarantee product suitability,
            quality, or performance. Always research and test gear before relying on it in wilderness settings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 6: No Endorsement -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">6. No Endorsement of Specific Trails</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            Inclusion of a trail on Summit Seeker does not constitute an endorsement, recommendation, or
            guarantee that the trail is safe, appropriate, or legal for your use. Trail difficulty ratings
            are subjective and based on general assessments‚Äîyour personal fitness, experience, weather conditions,
            and time of year significantly affect trail difficulty.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Some trails may cross private property, require permits, have seasonal closures, or be illegal
            to access. It is your responsibility to verify access rights and regulations before hiking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7: User-Generated Content -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">7. User-Generated Content</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            If we accept user comments, reviews, or trail reports in the future, such content represents
            the views of individual users, not Summit Seeker. We do not verify user-submitted information
            and are not responsible for its accuracy. Do not rely solely on user reviews for safety decisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8: Emergency Contact -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">8. Emergencies</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-orange-600">IN CASE OF EMERGENCY, CALL 911 IMMEDIATELY.</strong> Do not contact
            Summit Seeker for emergency assistance. We are not an emergency response service. Emergency contacts
            listed on trail pages are provided for informational purposes‚Äîprogram them into your phone before hiking.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-orange-50 p-4 rounded-lg mt-4">
            <p class="text-stone-800 font-semibold text-sm">
              üö® Emergency Preparedness Checklist:
            </p>
            <ul class="text-stone-700 text-sm mt-2 space-y-1 ml-6 list-disc">
              <li>Tell someone your hiking plans and expected return time</li>
              <li>Carry a charged phone with offline maps downloaded</li>
              <li>Bring the Ten Essentials (navigation, sun protection, insulation, illumination, first aid, fire, repair kit, nutrition, hydration, emergency shelter)</li>
              <li>Check weather forecasts and trail conditions before departing</li>
              <li>Know your limits and turn back if conditions deteriorate</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9: Changes to Disclaimer -->
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-stone-900 mb-4">9. Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to modify this disclaimer at any time without notice. Continued use of
            the Website after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated disclaimer. Check this page
            periodically for updates.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Final Statement -->
        <div class="bg-stone-900 text-white p-8 rounded-lg text-center mt-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-3">By Using This Website</h2>
          <p class="text-stone-300 mb-4">
            You acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to this disclaimer and our
            <a href="/terms" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Terms of Service</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm">
            Questions? <a href="/contact" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Contact us</a>
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose li {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
